name: Adam Masters
about: I am a junior College Scholar with a double major in Information Science. I currently work for Assist, the leading chatbot provider for messaging and voice. On campus, I am a member of Cornell Blockchain and Mundial FC. Outside of school I love photography and listening to music.

name: Aiden Yeonsuk Kim
about: I am a UX/UI/Product designer with a passion for building products that ease our complicated lives. I also have interests in UX of AR/VR/IoT and Interaction design. After spending two years in the military, I came back to Cornell to learn more and make an impact in the community.

name: Alexa Bren
about: I'm a UX designer with a CS background, and I love getting to work at the intersection of art, technology, and people. I also enjoy listening to music, dancing, rock climbing, photography, and bread.

name: Alice Zhou
hometown: Same as currently stated on site, Same as currently stated on site
about: Boba addict. Food fanatic. Traveling nomad. An overall lover of all good experiences, I enjoy everything from lining up for hours for a good slice of Cheeseboard pizza to spontaneously skydiving with randos to fangirling over seamless product experiences. Outside of classes, I'm most likely found working on DTI stuff in eHub.

name: Amanda Ong
about: I enjoy working on products with a real-world application, which why I really like DTI! Outside of classes, I’m also the tech lead for the Engineering Career Fair Team. I enjoy being active when I can. When I’m home, I like to bike around the neighborhood and I’m hoping to learn how to snowboard or ice-skate this year. I also enjoy a variety of music, but my favorites are Troye Sivan, Noah Kahan, and Shawn Mendes.

name: Andrew Gao
about: I'm freshman in the College of Arts & Sciences (currently) majoring in CS and Stats. I love CS for its broad applicability and ability to have a positive impact on people—I'm still exploring what I can do in the future! In my free time, I enjoy photography, graphic design, and volleyball.

name: Andrew Xiao
about: If playing oneself were a sport, Andrew would be an Olympic gold medalist. Entering Cornell, Andrew played himself into thinking computer science wouldn't be hard. As a sophomore, he played himself into adding a statistics major. When not landing himself in sticky situations, Andrew enjoys reading, dancing, and being extra with literally anyone. If you'd like to get to know Andrew, you can attend his office hours in Olin 7th floor stacks where he listens to kpop and stares out the window.

name: Andrew Yates
about: Most of my time is spent drinking coffee, doing research, or programming. I consider myself a backend developer, because that's what I like the most, but sometimes you can catch me mingling with the HTML and CSS. DTI is awesome because I can do both while impacting campus life! Research wise, I'm focused on the intersection of compsci and physics - so catch me doing weird math at PSB!

name: April Ye
about: I love exploring new coffee shops and insta-perfect alleyways, and my guilty pleasure is currently couch potato-ing and tuning into Asia's Next Top Model. On campus, I'm currently involved with Cornell Consulting Group and run my online shop Cottontil!

name: Aram Baghdassarian
about: Gosh, I feel like these always come off as so generic and cliche and have always wondered what I can do to make them seem less trite. I don't even know if people read these.

name: Ashley Ticzon
about: When I’m not hiking up the slope to get to class,  I enjoy singing and playing music. Also, I have a crazy good memory and can remember almost everything down to the smallest detail. And even though I grew up very accustomed to the warm California sunshine, I actually find the winters in Ithaca very enjoyable.

name: Ashrita Raman
about: Hi, I'm Ashrita! I am a sophomore majoring in computer science and minoring in music and linguistics. I'm passionate about using technology to create a positive social impact. At Cornell, I teach piano to undergraduates through the Cornell Piano Society and am also a member of the Cornell Symphony Orchestra. Outside of class, you can find me listening to 19th century Romantic music, reading Harry Potter, going on a run, or taking pictures of good food.

name: Ayesha Gagguturi
about: When I'm not doing an assignment for a class you can usually catch me updating my bullet journal or working on my calligraphy. Or you can find me at other clubs which are ACSU, SWE, SAC, figure skating and my favorite CDTI doing something to help the cornell community!

name: Boon Palipatana
about: I'm an Information Science Major concentrating in Data Science. I love working with data analytics and I also study web, mobile app, and game development. Outside of class, I spend time watching basketball, running at a reasonable pace, being an RA in the Low Rises, and bonding with the squirrels on campus.

name: Bryan Graeser
about: When I'm not in Duffield working on a CS pset or DTI, I enjoy working on creative writing pieces and going to the gym. I am also Co-Director of Hack4Impact, a nonprofit, social impact CS group on campus. In my free time, I like playing games with friends and showing people unsolicited pet photos.

name: Cedric Castillo
about: I first began designing in high school as a lighting designer for my school's theatrical production and am building upon this passion for making by studying how to design interactions that complement human behaviors. Outside of DTI, I am a project manager for the fashion/lifestyle magazine, Thread, and UX team member for a design group focused on improving campus spaces, Straight Edge.

name: David Chu
hometown: Taipei, Taiwan & Boston, MA & New York, NY & Rockville, MD
about: I liked Hans Zimmer but am more recently into Beethoven and Schubert; highly recommend giving Appassionata a listen. I enjoy light-tasting Taiwanese foods (bitter melon stew!) and gas stoves. My favorite pickles are Ba Tampte, half sour, only at Wegmans. Like cucumbers, but with garlic.

name: Dray Farley
about: I love working on software that solves real problems, whether it be on campus, in the fitness industry, or in social impact. I primarily work on back-end but love to explore new frameworks and tech stacks! Outside of tech, I am an avid hip-hop and (unfortunately) New York Knicks fan. I also enjoy reading and going to the gym in my free time.

name: Emily Chan
about: Leave as is (i just filled this out to put a new photo. also my photo seems to be showing on Erin Chen's profile)

name: Evan Welsh
about: I'm a sophomore in the College of Arts and Sciences majoring in Computer Science. In my free time I love exploring all sorts of wild technologies. My adventures in Vue.js in fact led to this very site to use it. I've worked within frontend web, backend, and mobile spheres and enjoy periodically switching things up to get a better sense of new and especially emerging platforms. Outside of DTI I enjoy singing in Cornell Chorale, studying Latin, and experimenting with gluten-free recipes among other things.

name: Flora Liu
about: Hi, I'm Flora! I am currently studying Information Science in CAS, with concentrations in UI/UX and Digital Culture and Production. In my free time you can find me binging Tasty videos, not doing work, and drinking boba (30% sugar light ice ofc).

name: Gleni Kodra
about: I specialize in Human Capital, Team Psychology, and Diversity + Inclusion studies. Beyond the DTI Business Team, and I am the President of Northeast Ohio at Cornell University, and a Peer Advisor at Cornell Career Services. f you want to talk about greek food, shopping malls, pro wrestling, or the Cleveland Browns, reach out to me!

name: Ishika Jain
about: I am currently a freshman majoring in computer science in the College of Arts and Sciences. In my free time, you can find me performing as part of Cornell’s Indian Classical Dance group, Cornell Nazaqat,  organizing a Society of Women Engineers event or watching one of the many TV shows on ABC. I am excited to explore the design and development side of applications. I am always Down to Integrate (DTI) design and development to create applications that help to add to the Big Red experience!

name: Jagger Brulato
about: I'm a Computer Science student and developer for Cornell DTI. I'm a musician (piano and guitar), and I produce jazz, r&b, and hip hop music. I get a bit too excited about quantum and music theory, though I am also the type of person that's happy spending hours playing Legend of Zelda.

name: Jesse Mansoor
about: I am studying information science and concentrating in user experience. I am especially interested in how technology can be harnessed to improve efficiency and productivity of teams and individuals. I also study Spanish and spent last spring semester in Seville, Spain. In addition to my academics I love to play tennis and lacrosse and explore Ithaca.

name: Jessica Chen
about: I love exploring/developing ways that technology can contribute to community impact. Aside from CDTI, I am also the philanthropy chair for Alpha Omega Epsilon (Cornell's engineering sorority), a member of the club tennis team, an AEW facilitator, and a CS course consultant! In my free time, I enjoy hiking, hammocking, adventuring, being an Edthusiast, and chasing sunsets.

name: Jessica Hong
about: Jessica Hong is a junior studying computer science. She is currently researching fairness in ranking algorithms and is passionate about using CS for social impact.

name: Jessica Zhao
about: I'm a CS major with a side interest for Psychology. On campus, I'm an Engineering Peer Advisor and a member of Cornell Undergraduate Asia Business Society. This past summer, I worked as a SWE at VMware. In my free time, I enjoy working out, reading conspiracy theories, and exploring Ithaca!

name: Joaquin Amante
about: On campus, I sing with Jazz Voices and publicize stuff for the International Students Union. I also lead design for Ezra Box. Lately, I've been trying to make a short film.

name: Julian Londono
about: Productivity is a lifestyle: when I'm not working with my team on CU Reviews you'll find me working on Info Sci research, exploring curiosity-driven side projects, mountain biking, or playing frisbee.  I'm always trying to learn more about photography, drones, and guitar playing.

name: Justin Tran
about: I have been a developer on Samwise since Fall 2016 and am currently a TA for Trends in Web Development.  I can generally be found in Duffield going through existential crises about my potential future in the tech industry, or playing piano in various places for the Cornell Anything Goes Musical Theatre Troupe.

name: Kaitlyn Son
minor: Possibly Human Development and or DEA, lets see
about: NY based designer with a passion for all things creative, learning, and corgis. At any given party find me by the guac.

name: Kathleen Xu
about: I'm happiest when I'm creating, whether that be working on an app, writing a story or knitting a scarf. I'm currently a part of DTI (obviously), Cornell Eastern Music Ensemble, and the Cornell Lunatic. When I'm not trying to power through all my work, you can find me drinking boba tea, watching anime, or obsessing over food (maybe even all three).

name: Kathy Wang
about: I'm a Cornell MPS student, and I love how UX design allows me to combine my analytical and creative sides. At Cornell, I've been a part of eLab, Club Swim, Medium Design Collective, Kappa Phi Lambda, and The Cornell Daily Sun. I love listening to Lana Del Rey, Billie Eilish, and Zedd. Outside of classes, you can find me eating pasta (I love carbs), FaceTiming my Golden Retriever (as he ignores my existence), or attending music festivals.

name: Kaushik Ravikumar
about: I'm an avid developer who loves seeing software used to solve problems. I'm also intrigued by the idea of Smart Cities and using the internet of things to improve our current infrastructures. Besides that I love exploring nature, traveling, listening to music and dropping my own fire mixtapes.

name: Laura Sizemore
about: I am a sophomore studying Computer Science in the College of Engineering. I enjoy using technology to develop a positive impact on my community and beyond. I have experience in full-stack development and data analysis through her past internships. When I'm not coding, I enjoy reading sci-fi novels, listening to music, and spending time with friends

name: Lisa LaBarbera
about: Lisa LaBarbera is a junior majoring in Information Science. She is from the small town by NYC. Her interests include photography, traveling and design! On campus, she is a member of APO, WICC, and is a violinist in the Cornell Chamber Orchestra. In her free time she loves to explore, play music, and take pictures.

name: Matthew Barker
about: I have most of my fun outside of classes (who doesn't), from developing and designing apps to doing creative writing and playing music. I'm also a member of Cornell App Development, Cornell Lunatic Humor Magazine, and the Big Red Bands. I like Daft Punk, ping pong, and lists of three. And I very much enjoy Slacking in DTI.

name: Matthew Coufal
about: I'm a San Diego native, big tennis fan, ping pong fanatic, and piano soloist. Although it might not seem like it, I'm also 25% Puerto Rican. By the way, I love to make apps.

name: Matthew Epstein
about: From new technologies for web and mobile development to overloading credit-hours, I am always learning. I am an aggressive YouTube consumer currently infatuated with items created with various resins and wood. I enjoy watching people play video games, am a professional (shower) singer, and am an advocate of the Oxford comma.

name: Megan She
about: I'm a junior English major, but I identify as the ampersand in Arts & Sciences. I love working an espresso bar, making far too many Spotify playlists, and dabbling in the sublime. I'm also a member of Cornell Mars Rover, Science Olympiad at Cornell, and Alpha Phi Omega. I'm always looking for more niche academia, another stamp in my passport, and the best brie out there. And I'm always a sucker for bad jokes.

name: Megan Yin
about: I began coding when I was 13 years old and since then I have developed my skills through computational biology research, robotics, project teams, and free-lance web development. Through these experiences, I’ve developed an interest in robotics, machine learning, venture capital, front-end development and financial modeling. In addition, I’ve discovered the best code is written together and I love spending weekends planning and hosting collegiate hackathons with BigRed//Hacks or working with my team Cornell Design & Tech Initiative on campus.

name: Michael Xing
about: Michael is a full stack developer who enjoys building things for people to use. He primarily works in Java and web technologies, but dabbles with anything and everything that looks remotely interesting. When not coding, he enjoys helping aspiring developers while TAing 2110 / 2112, playing the piano, or playing video games (not necessarily in that order of priority).

name: Michelle Park
about: Hi! I'm Michelle and I love designing digital solutions. Outside of designing and school, I love shopping for almost anything and everything. I also love exploring new spaces that are unfamiliar to me.

name: Neha Rao
about: I love to stay busy on campus! Other than being a part of this amazing project team, I'm Musical Director of Cornell's Original Musical Theatre Troupe, Anything Goes. In my free time, I enjoy singing, playing guitar, going to Zumba classes, bingeing Netflix, and eating ice cream!

name: Qichen Hu
about: Talk is cheap. I’ll show ya the code.

name: Raymone Radi
about: I am a junior studying Computer Science. I love to find creative solutions to difficult problems, and think CS is the perfect tool to do so!

name: Rebecca Fu
about: I’m passionate about sustainability, technology, social impact, and oolong milk tea. I joined DTI to meet a huge group of people who share my interests in creating technology to help the greater community. Outside of DTI, I am also a member of The Wardrobe and CUSD. If I'm not hiding in 3rd floor Mann, you can probably find me playing tennis, fencing, dancing, or catching up with friends.

name: Robert Villaluz
about: Bobby is a sophomore studying computer science in the College of Arts and Sciences. He is passionate about cybersecurity and developing software for positive community impact. When Bobby isn't grinding in the stacks, he loves to surf, read and play ping pong. A former 8-ball champ, he decided to leave the solids and stripes behind to become the world's best coder.

name: Rodrigo Taipe
about: I am a programmer and math enthusiast who loves both the applied and theoretical side of computer science. I enjoy playing and watching basketball games as well as analyzing NBA statistics. I also play Magic The Gathering and similar trading card games. As someone with Peruvian heritage, I enjoy all things Peru especially the food and tourist attractions.

name: Ronni Mok
about: DTI has become a place where I can personally gain exposure to design and development, while also employing my strengths to positively impact my community. Other than DTI, I am also on the executive boards of the Cornell International Business Association and the Cornell International Affairs Review.

name: Ryan Slama
about: Hey! I'm overly passionate about semi-eclectic music, black coffee, tea, politics, board games, oxford commas, and pretty much anything else at the intersection of hipster and basic. This summer I'm returning to Slack's Product Security team in San Francisco.

name: Sam Zhou
about: Sam is a full stack web developer with extensive experience in backend development in Kotlin/Java and frontend development with Angular Framework. Sam is interested in designing and developing extensible and scalable software systems as well as programming languages.

name: Sanjana Seshadri
about: Besides designing, I love all things music and dance! On campus, I am a member of Cornell Anjali, an Indian classical dance team, and a member of Forté Campus at Cornell, a professional business organization. In my free time, I enjoy exploring new places to eat and drink coffee, finding fun things to take pictures of, and learning how to play my favorite songs on the piano.

name: Shane Yun
about: Bello! I am an aspiring product designer who wants to create a better world for the people I love. I'm involved in other design teams outside of DTI which include Medium Design Collective and Cornell Fashion Collective. I love taking and editing photos and learning about fashion.

name: Shefali Agarwal
about: I am a member of Big Red Raas, Alpha Phi Omega, SWE, WICC, ACSU, UWC Club, Society for India and DTI of course! I enjoy dancing, singing, sketching and music. I also love to hang out with people and have a good chill time!

name: Sonya Tao
about: I am most excited when exploring and piloting new technologies to push a business forward. In addition to DTI, I was also part of Smart Woman Securities and CUWinds. I love Costco, chicken, wine, food shows, and finding new music. Before I retire, I hope to go on more adventures to unexpected places. And of course, I believe that laughter is the best medicine!

name: Sophia Wang
about: Hi, I'm Sophia! I am interested in storytelling through design and creating products for people. Outside of class, I can be found petting a dog or running outside. I am obsessed with my Cockapoo puppy, Thai food, traveling, and fake plants (because who has time for real ones?).

name: Stacy Wei
about: Stacy is currently a sophomore studying Computer Science. She was born and raised in a suburb near Chicago, IL. At Cornell, Stacy is involved in the Aguaclara Project Team, Chinese Student Association, and Society of Women Engineers. In her free time, Stacy loves playing tennis, listening to music, and exploring the GORGEous nature in Ithaca

name: Trey Burrell
about: I am the Secretary of the Cornell Chapter of the National Society of Black Engineers.  I am an aspiring entrepreneur and software developer with experience in software development, equity research, and leadership.  I have interned at T. Rowe Price as an Equity Research Analyst and Fixt as a Software Developer.  I will be interning at Uber Technologies Inc. in San Francisco over the Summer of 2019.  In my free time I like to do music production and gaming.

name: Vanessa Wang
about: Hi! I'm a sophomore studying computer science who is exicited to spend another year with DTI! Whenever I'm not studying or coding, I devote my free time to volunteering around campus, crocheting stuffed animals, and taking naps (like every other student).

name: Vivian Shiu
about: Catch me drinking an açai smoothie in Olin or petting dogs around campus. I love to play soccer, piano, and doodle everywhere. I'm passionate about the unknown effects design can have on a person's daily life. I'm also a self proclaimed professional napper :)

name: Will Spencer
about: Besides DTI, I am involved with Girls Who Code on campus, where I help high-school students learn and appreciate the basics of programming. Besides developing, I spend my time gaming and following politics, so I can commonly be found yelling at my computer due to a broken controller or scandalous news story.

name: Yisu Zheng
about: I enjoy meeting new people, exploring new places and procrastinating (are they related?!)  I am also a photographer at Cornell Daily Sun and a member of ACSU.

name: Yuchang Zhou
about: I enjoy creation, especially the process of realizing one crazy idea. As both software engineer and designer I am actively involved in projects that develop cool products -- mobile apps, web apps, online game, etc. I have been a freelance illustrator since my entry to college and have recently collaborated with my favorite pop singer's concert team! I also design for Cornell Chinese Drama Society, Association of Computer Science Undergraduates, Cornell University Sustainable Design and some school magazines.

name: Yvonne Chan
about: As much as I enjoy designing and developing apps, I also enjoy nature walking, creative writing, and meeting new people. Apart from being on DTI, I am a member of the Assorted Aces Dance Team and the WICC Photo Committee. When I'm not working in Duffield, I'm finding the best places to nap on campus and trying to catch up on Brooklyn Nine-Nine!
